<DocsPage
  title="Add package from link"
  description="Paste a GitHub or Git URL, generate the right nodus add command, then run it locally."
>
  <p>
    Nodus does not need a registry to install packages. If you have a GitHub repo link,
    Git URL, or <code>owner/repo</code> reference, you can turn it directly into the right
    <code>nodus add</code> command.
  </p>

  <p>Use the package page to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>paste a package reference and normalize it into the right source</li>
    <li>optionally append <code>--adapter</code> for the target tool</li>
    <li>copy the exact command you should run in your repo</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Use the live generator at <a href="/packages/">/packages/</a>.</p>
</DocsPage>
